1 Introduction
1.1 Release note
This version is under user testing, working for VW polarion project only
and will be updated for other projects.
Also this version is adaptered per VW polarion folder structure, which means
that SWA baselines is separated in one folder also SWREQ

1.2 Purpose
Main purpose of this tool is to automate review process, which is defined in
review checklist which provides in this reports
1.2.1 - Bi-Directional treasability between SWREQ WI , DWIs and SWC WIs
1.2.2 - Bi-Directional treasability between system function and SWC and
system function documsnt status
1.2.3 - Trasability matrix data of all SWA WIs
1.2.4 - Consistency check between SWA baseline and SWREQ baseline
1.2.5 - Delta report between different SWA baselines
1.3 Restrictions - important information
SWA baseline separated in polarion in one folder for each release
SWREQ baseline separated in polarion in one folder for each release
SWA elements referenced in SWA element

2.2 Tool Inputs
Inputs is like the following
2.2.1 - polarion Username
2.2.2 - polarion password
2.2.3 - polarion project till now it still working only in VW project
2.2.4 - polarion release baseline folder
ex: 24_11_1_19_p330
you will need to copy that from polarion like [fig-3]
2.2.5 - polarion Requirement Baseline folder
Like 2.2.4 you need to get it from polarion
2.2.6 - polarion old release baseline folder
which is the SWA baseline which you need to generate delta report
between it and current polarion release baseline folder selected in
(2.2.4)

2.3 Reports Description
Tool mainly generate 5 reports, each report has sheet which called
execution details which is show execution data like
who generate this report ,SWA baseline ,SWREQ baseline ..etc
the reported as following :
2.3.1 - Req_SWC_Bi_Directional
as shown in [Fig-4] the main sheets generated
KPI
SWREQ VS SWC traceability
DWI VS SWC traceability
SWC VS (DWI and SWREQ ) traceability
